<doc id="1211184" wikidata="Q7416745" url="?curid=1211184" title="Sandra Roper">
<text>Sandra Elena Roper (born c. December 29, 1956) is an American civil rights lawyer, who had an unsuccessful candidacy for district attorney in Brooklyn, New York against former King&#x27;s County district attorney Charles J. Haynes, in 2001 before making a successful run for judge in 2017. She is currently an active civil court judge in Kings County, New York. She has served in criminal court and civil court.

